    <p>It has to be a tide that re­ally lifts all boats... so that there’s some­thing in it for ev­ery­body, so that peo­ple of colour see their prospects im­prov­ing.</p>
    <p>But also, so that the white work­ing class in so-called Rust Belt ar­eas of de­clin­ing man­u­fac­tur­ing see new hopes for mean­ing­fully re­mu­ner­a­tive work, bet­ter lives, bet­ter ed­u­ca­tional prospects and more dig­nity.’’</p>
    <p>DEMOC­RACY SCHOLAR AND AU­THOR LARRY DI­A­MOND, on how in­com­ing pres­i­dent Joe Bi­den has to gen­er­ate suf­fi­cient, broadly dis­trib­uted and in­clu­sive eco­nomic growth.</p>


